      {
        "id": 1696965,
        "name": "Paul H Galli",
        "username": "Paul_H_Galli",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/paul_h_galli/{size}/859_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-28T15:03:26.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong><span class=\"bbcode-u\">1988 Mount Eden Estate Chard</span></strong><br>\nHad this with lobster for my 65th birthday.<br>\nA REALLY crumbly cork took 5 minutes to extract.<br>\nWas concerned the wine could be spoiled.<br>\nOne sniff dispelled all worries.<br>\nMature golden color.<br>\nRich nose of lemons and grilled nuts.<br>\nChewy, nutty, green lime fruit with undertones of caramel and toasty oak.<br>\nA fine long, dry, anise finish with good acid remaining to keep it zippy.<br>\nStill another sterling example of an aged CA Chard from the great Mount Eden! <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/9/99a8907a1d5b3c023582052741dc72dc9823c044.gif\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" alt=\"[worship.gif]\" title=\"worship\"><br>\nWell stored examples should hold for a few more years, but my advice is to pound away Matey\u2026<br>\nWould LOVE to try this in magnum!<br>\nBravo for Jeffrey! (Once again)<br>\n[94+ pts]</p>\n<p>TTT</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
