      {
        "id": 1697227,
        "name": "Paul H Galli",
        "username": "Paul_H_Galli",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/paul_h_galli/{size}/859_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-28T21:57:05.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Joe S.\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Joe S.:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Happy 65th birthday and thanks for posting, Paul.  This is one of my favorite chardonnays and I\u2019m glad to know I can lay some of these down for quite a while\u2026 <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Several years ago, I bought two mixed cases of Mt Eden Chard from the 80s and 90s from K&amp;L for a song.<br>\nI\u2019ve consumed half of them.<br>\nEVERY bottle have been fine to great.<br>\nNobody in CA makes Chard that ages consistently well as Da Mount\u2026</p>\n<p>TTT</p>",
